Humala Offered Economy, Trade Ministries to Toledo, Peru.21 Says

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-06-08T14:33:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/humala-offered-economy-trade-ministries-to-toledo-peru-21-says.html
Peruvian President-elect Ollanta Humala offered six Cabinet posts, including finance minister and
trade minister, to the party of former President  Alejandro Toledo , Peru.21  reported .  Toledo’s Peru Posible party is assessing a political
alliance with Humala and hasn’t made a decision on joining his
government, the Lima-based newspaper said, citing people it
didn’t name.  Humala’s proposal, which he made before winning the
election, also comprised the Production, Transport, Justice and
Education Ministries and posts at the central bank, tax
collection agency and state bank Banco de la Nacion, Peru.21
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
